_400/profile-displayphoto-shrink_400_400/0/1517699579036?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=cTCMjbDDNuUv3ezRYPxwQetHrLE_1uOdHcrJLkrUQVI", "profilePicHighQuality": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4E03AQFkrmz8w2ry5w/profile-displayphoto-shrink_400_400/profile-displayphoto-shrink_400_400/0/1517699579036?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=cTCMjbDDNuUv3ezRYPxwQetHrLE_1uOdHcrJLkrUQVI", "publicIdentifier": "richard-deutl-7a67044", "recommendations/0/context": "Richard managed Rg directly", "recommendations/0/date": "July 10, 2016", "recommendations/0/description": "I have worked with RG at The St. Regis Chengdu. RG was selected amongst many candidates for this position as in the interview already he demonstrated passion for the hotel industry, passion for luxury and passion to ensure that the opening of The St. Regis Chengdu would be extremely successful and burnt into all stakeholders' minds, especially of course the local, national and international media colleagues.\nRG exceeded our expectations; he created and formed an amazing marketing team, was a most valuable member of the leadership team which always could count on his input and support, worked very well together with our brand team to open the hotel in full compliance with the famed St. Regis brand values, basically led the entire grand opening event as liaison with all involved in a very independent manner, and always efficiently communicating with all stakeholders.\nRG was the perfect fit for this opening and I only can recommend RG to any future employer who is looking for an energetic, passionate, effective team player and team leader who is supposed to be able to adjust to new environments, perfectly well connected and thanks to his previous experience can enlarge the horizon of the usual Marketing scopes found.  ", "recommendations/0/name": "Rg Orense", "recommendations/0/subtitle": "Leading Digital Transformation, Tech For Good Advocate, ESG Communications, Aiming To Be A StartUp Trailblazer", "recommendations/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/rgorense/", "recommendations/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAASb820BTAb7J2UeeonvOjEZIfjw4Ewkiwg", "recommendations/1/context": "Richard managed Sunny directly", "recommendations/1/date": "May 13, 2015", "recommendations/1/description": "I have worked with Sunny basically from day 1 of my appointment as opening GM for The Westin Nanjing. By then, Sunny was still working as Controller for the New Built and Transitions team and thus was supporting me right away. Sunny demonstrated then already one of her strengths,  strategic thinking; well balancing the needs of all stakeholders whilst keeping a clear focus on the direction to go, on the goal to be accomplished.\n\nIt was therefore an easy decision to hire Sunny into my property and thus take more advantage of those skills and discover more like the ability to hire the right talents, guide them and give them space and freedom to successfully develop. This gave Sunny the opportunity also to take over operational responsibilities as well as serving as main liaison between all main stakeholders.\n\nShe guided the team very well in maintaining cost discipline and also gave constantly constructive suggestions on how to improve the revenue side thus helping to exceed certain financial KPIs at a very early stage; Sunny set a great foundation which the hotel could benefit from long after Sunny decided to pursue other opportunities.\n\nWhoever would be looking for a talent with such qualities as well as likes to work together with a very kind, calm, respectful lady who also values family and respects this in other people, would not regret to have hired Sunny.", "recommendations/1/name": "Sunny X.", "recommendations/1/subtitle": "20 years of Hospitality Industry experience with world-leading groups, including Marriott International, Fairmont Hotels, Starwood and Accor in operating and pre-opening environments as well as Corporate Office.", "recommendations/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/sunny-x-3234b937/", "recommendations/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAe6GYsBWipUK0qXSlH54rAtKpm_OF7VrWs", "recommendations/2/context": "Richard was Ela's client", "recommendations/2/date": "May 1, 2014", "recommendations/2/description": "I can recommend  Ela as determined, result oriented representative of her company; she showed passion and knowledge for all, the industry, the company and the products she was responsible for; I can see Ela's social style and professionalism fit for any Retailer/Wholesaler and because of her determination for quality, could imagine her well in the luxury industry.", "recommendations/2/name": "Ela Mokrzan", "recommendations/2/subtitle": "International Strategic Partnerships Director", "recommendations/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/ela-mokrzan-09648b14/", "recommendations/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAALrArIB3veux2KRXX2qBdzLSofNipOIoyE", "recommendations/3/context": "Richard managed Sabine directly", "recommendations/3/date": "June 29, 2013", "recommendations/3/description": "This is to testimony the success that Sabine showed as a driver of key results and leader of the Reservations team whilst working at the Sheraton Airport Hotel Charles de Gaulle.\n\nKnowledgeable of the specific situations that an airport hotel brings with itself, the team under Sabine's leadership not only managed well the sudden demand changes very efficiently but most importantly, leveraged the opportunities that come with it and drove the RPI to unprecendently outstanding performances.\n\nThis was only possible through Sabine's calm yet well determined leadership personality, outstanding teamwork, communication skills, understanding of key drivers and enthusiasm.\n\nSabine served for me as example for many Revenue Directors I worked together with afterwards; not easy to find similar driven and successful people like Sabine.", "recommendations/3/name": "Sabine Levasseur", "recommendations/3/subtitle": "Au plaisir de vous accueillir lors de votre venue dans le 